---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Claudient — community Claude Code knowledge base"
  description="Claudient is an open-source community knowledge base for Claude Code. 277+ skills, 95+ agents, MIT licensed, backed by Uitbreiden. Not affiliated with Anthropic."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="container-page py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="pill mb-6">MIT · Community · v1.8</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.05]">
        Domain expertise for Claude Code, built by the community.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        Claudient is a knowledge system — skills, agents, hooks, rules, workflows, and
        prompts that give Claude Code instant domain expertise across stacks, industries,
        and languages. Free to use, open to contributions, MIT licensed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What it is -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <div class="grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">What Claudient is</h2>
          <div class="prose text-sm">
            <p>
              Claude Code is a powerful coding assistant — but without context, it
              doesn't know your stack, your industry, or your workflows. You end up
              re-explaining the same things at the start of every session.
            </p>
            <p>
              Claudient solves that. It's a community-maintained library of
              drop-in knowledge files that activate automatically when they're
              relevant: a FastAPI skill fires when you open a Python project, a
              legal review agent activates when you ask about contracts, a
              cash-flow skill activates when a small business owner asks about
              QuickBooks.
            </p>
            <p>
              The result: Claude knows your domain from the first message, without
              you having to teach it every session.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Who it's for</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { audience: "Developers and vibe coders", desc: "200+ framework and stack skills for backend, DevOps, AI engineering, data, and database work." },
              { audience: "AI product builders", desc: "RAG, LangGraph, Claude API patterns with prompt caching, MCP server builder." },
              { audience: "Small business owners", desc: "Plain-English skills for invoicing, cash flow, Shopify, SOPs, and 14 vertical industries. No terminal required." },
              { audience: "GTM and RevOps teams", desc: "HubSpot MCP, SDR agent, lead enrichment, email automation, CRM hygiene." },
              { audience: "Finance and legal professionals", desc: "DCF models, contract review, GDPR, SOC 2 — with mandatory human review gates built in." },
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex gap-3">
                <span
                  class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full inline-flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold"
                  style="background-color: var(--color-accent-soft); color: var(--color-accent);"
                >
                  →
                </span>
                <span class="text-sm">
                  <strong>{item.audience}</strong>
                  <span style="color: var(--color-muted);"> — {item.desc}</span>
                </span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Relationship to Anthropic -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Relationship to Anthropic and Claude Code</h2>
      <div class="prose text-sm">
        <p>
          Claudient is a community project. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by,
          or in any way connected to Anthropic. Claude and Claude Code are Anthropic
          products.
        </p>
        <p>
          Claudient extends Claude Code the same way any knowledge base or dotfile
          extends a tool — by giving it more context. The skills, agents, and hooks
          here are plain text files that Claude Code ingests. No modifications to
          Claude itself, no API access beyond what you already have.
        </p>
        <p>
          Anthropic launched an official{" "}
          <strong>Claude for Small Business</strong> product layer in May 2026 with
          15 workflows. Claudient extends that with 30+ additional skills covering
          the long tail of verticals and operator workflows that the official product
          doesn't yet address.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Open source -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">Open source, MIT licensed</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        {[
          { title: "Free to use", desc: "Install, use, fork, and modify. The MIT license places no restrictions on personal or commercial use." },
          { title: "Community-powered", desc: "Every skill lives in one markdown file. Anyone can contribute — and merged skills get featured in Most Popular." },
          { title: "Five languages", desc: "All content ships in English, French, German, Dutch, and Spanish. Hook scripts are English-only — shell is universal." },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card p-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- By the numbers -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">By the numbers</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5">
      {[
        { count: "277+", label: "Skills" },
        { count: "95+", label: "Agents" },
        { count: "30+", label: "Hooks" },
        { count: "31+", label: "MCP configs" },
        { count: "5", label: "Languages" },
      ].map((stat) => (
        <div
          class="rounded-lg p-5 text-center"
          style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
        >
          <div
            class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1"
            style="color: var(--color-accent);"
          >
            {stat.count}
          </div>
          <div class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{stat.label}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Backed by Uitbreiden -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Backed by Uitbreiden</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Claudient is maintained by{" "}
          <a
            href="https://uitbreiden.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            style="color: var(--color-accent);"
          >Uitbreiden</a> — a company that builds AI products and B2B tools with
          developer communities. The repo is open source and community contributions
          are the primary growth mechanism, but Uitbreiden maintains the core,
          handles releases, and keeps the npm package live.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-8" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          If you want to go beyond contributing to the repo and actually build AI
          products or B2B solutions with the team, reach out directly via the
          Uitbreiden website.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="https://uitbreiden.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="btn-primary"
          >
            uitbreiden.com
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.reddit.com/r/uitbreiden/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="btn-ghost"
          >
            Reddit — r/uitbreiden
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://www.youtube.com/@UITBREIDEN"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="btn-ghost"
          >
            YouTube — @UITBREIDEN
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="container-page py-20">
    <div class="max-w-xl">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Get started now</h2>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        One command, 30 seconds, 277+ skills ready to go.
      </p>
      <div
        class="flex items-center px-4 py-3 rounded-md font-mono text-sm mb-4 w-fit"
        style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
      >
        <span style="color: var(--color-subtle);">$</span>&nbsp;npx claudient add all
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a href="/install/" class="btn-primary">Installation guide</a>
        <a href="/contribute/" class="btn-ghost">Contribute a skill</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
